cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with stereo image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset for stereo image SR, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to the cs.CV category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The parallax-attention mechanism introduced in the paper involves handling disparities between stereo images, which could potentially fall under the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
